    "plan_content": "Here's the full implementation plan for `uv cache stats`:\n\n---\n\n## What will be built\n\n`uv cache stats [--human]` — a new subcommand (gated behind `--preview` / `PreviewFeature::CacheStats`) that prints one row per cache bucket then a Total row. `--human` / `-H` / `--human-readable` formats sizes as `117.7MiB` instead of raw bytes, identical to the flag on `uv cache size`.\n\n---\n\n## 9 files to touch\n\n| # | File | Change |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | `crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs` | Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` feature flag + `\"cache-stats\"` string mappings |\n| 2 | `crates/uv-cache/src/lib.rs` | Add `pub fn name(self) -> &'static str` to `CacheBucket` (returns clean labels like `\"wheels\"`, `\"sdists\"`, etc.) |\n| 3 | `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` | Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand`; add `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct |\n| 4 | `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` | **New file** — core implementation; iterates all 11 buckets (including `Python`, which `CacheBucket::iter()` omits), calls `DiskUsage` per bucket, prints aligned table |\n| 5 | `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs` | Register `mod cache_stats` + re-export `cache_stats` |\n| 6 | `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` | Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats` |\n| 7 | `crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs` | Add `cache_stats()` command builder + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` snapshot filter |\n| 8 | `crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs` | Add `mod cache_stats` under the same feature gates as `mod cache_size` |\n| 9 | `crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs` | **New file** — 3 integration tests: empty cache (exact snapshot), raw bytes after install (filtered), human-readable after install (filtered) |\n\nNo new crate dependencies — the existing `diskus` and `uv-console::human_readable_bytes` (already used by `cache_size`) cover everything.",
